Full Description: Bric helps you accurately plan your team’s calendar, so you can confidently get back to doing the work you love. Enter Bric. You need an accurate prediction of what’s around the corner. And you need to be able to make decisions before the chaos. Bric helps you accurately plan your team’s calendar, so you can confidently get back to doing the work you love. They know what it is like to run a creative agency. Bric was built from their experiences running design firms, marketing agencies, software dev shops, and predictive analytics consultancies. They started Bric because they were tired of spending all day in traffic meetings, balancing spreadsheets, and updating whiteboards. Even with all of this work, they still didn’t have the information they needed to run their businesses. They started their creative agencies because they enjoyed the work they did. People hired us because they were good at the work they loved. However, as their agencies grew they spent less time creating and more time managing time. Until, that was all they did. Their systems are designed to carry onboard professional sensors that give back data and measurements and not only pictures or videos (e.g. they use IR cameras with radiometric output). For many people the primary criteria to evaluate the effectiveness of a solution is to evaluate the performances compared with the marketplace but this approach often does not satisfy a second parameter that define the trade-off for the use of drones in the real word: the safety. Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: SeeYouThen new app is all about connecting people, places and events.  Its a social platform that allows you to connect with friends, but the real unique aspect is the ability to connect to places and events in real-time.  Whether you created the SeeYouThen Exchange or SYTE for short or you join one, you can connect and share with Who's There! SeeYouThen is all about connecting with friends and groups of friends.  You can join or create cool and unique virtual connection points called Exchanges or SYTES for short. - INVITE YOUR FRIENDS. I know… not another social network. Group Chatting is ok, but why not create a cool space just for that group that needs to be connected. - CREATE EXCHANGES FOR GROUPS OF PEOPLE, PLACES, AND EVENTS.  Connect your groups, favorite places, and especially events ( big or small) (A Wedding to a Saturday night out with friends). It takes under a minute to create a new exchange (syte). - DIRECT MESSAGES If you have an internet connection you can send messages to your friends. No need to worry about your SMS plans, just chat directly with friends.. - PHOTOs MIXER Stay in the mix with your friends’ photos as they post. But wait, you can also filter friend’s photos. You can still be friends, but not have to see all their photos all the time. You know the ones. - ACTIVITY WALL (ALL ACTIVITY AND EXCHANGES) Your wall keeps you in the loop of what is going on across all exchanges that you have created or joined. - NOTIFICATIONS You decide how you want to be notified. Just go to notification preferences and turn on the activities that you want to know about right away and those that you don’t. You're in control. Let’s get started and get connecting! Download the app, then the first stop is to join SeeYouThen’s exchange to keep up on all the updates and what we’re up to.

Description: Risk management company
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Fcstone Group Inc is a integrated commodity risk management company providing risk management consulting and transaction execution services to commercial commodity intermediaries, end-users and producers. They assist primarily middle-market customers in optimizing their profit margins and mitigating their exposure to commodity price risk. In addition to their risk management consulting services, they operate one of the leading independent clearing and execution platforms for exchange-traded futures and options contracts. They serve more than 7,500 customers, and in the twelve months ended November 30, 2006, executed 50.2 million derivative contracts in the exchange-traded and over-the-counter (“OTC”) markets. As a natural complement to their commodity risk management consulting services, they also assist their customers with the financing, transportation and merchandising of their physical commodity requirements and inventories. Their net income increased $8.7 million, or 131.8%, from $6.6 million in fiscal 2005 to $15.3 million in fiscal 2006, and increased $2.9 million, or 85.3% from $3.4 million in the three months ended November 30, 2005, to $6.3 million in the three months ended November 30, 2006.
